Open Data Armenia

Purpose

This repository is part of the Open Data Armenia Project, which aims to collect, structure, and make accessible open metadata related to Armenian history, culture, and heritage from public digital collections.

The dataset included in this repository contains metadata records extracted from Hispana (Spain's National Digital Heritage Aggregator) via the Europeana API.

Use of Metadata

The metadata contained in this repository (including titles, descriptions, dates, identifiers, and links) is free to use, share, analyze, and redistribute for:

- research

- education

- digital humanities projects

- data analysis

- non-commercial or commercial reuse

Rights to Original Content

This repository does not claim ownership over the digital objects or cultural materials referenced in the dataset.

All copyright, intellectual property rights, and usage restrictions related to the original materials remain with the source institutions, cultural heritage organizations, and content providers that contributed the materials to Hispana and Europeana.

Users must consult the rights statements and licenses associated with each original item before reusing images, documents, or other digital content.

Scope of This License

This license applies only to the structured dataset and code contained in this repository.

It does not grant rights to:

- images

- digitized manuscripts

- books

- artworks

- archival materials

or any other primary cultural heritage objects linked through the dataset.

Data Sources

Primary data sources include:

Hispana – https://hispana.mcu.es

Europeana – https://www.europeana.eu

Both platforms aggregate content from numerous cultural heritage institutions.